1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 54-06 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to state contracts with certain companies that boycott energy, mining,
3 and production agriculture; and to provide for application.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 54-06 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
6 and enacted as follows:
7 Prohibition on contracts - Boycotting critical state sectors .
8 1. As used in this section:
9 a. "Boycott" means without any ordinary business purpose, refusing to deal with,
10 terminating business activities with, or otherwise taking any action intended to
11 penalize, inflict economic harm on, or limit commercial relations with a company
12 because the company:
13 (1) Engages in the exploration, production, use, transportation, sale, or
14 manufacturing of fossil fuel-based energy, timber, minerals, hydroelectric
15 power, nuclear energy, or mining and does not commit or pledge to meet
16 environmental standards beyond applicable federal and state law;
17 (2) Engages in production agriculture;
18 (3) Engages in, facilitates, or supports the manufacture, import, distribution,
19 marketing, advertising, sale, or lawful use of firearms, ammunition, or
20 components, parts, and accessories of firearms or ammunition; or
21 (4) Does business with a company engaged in the activities described in this
22 subdivision.
23 b. "Company" means a for-profit organization, association, corporation, partnership,
24 joint venture, limited partnership, limited liability partnership, or limited liability
